description.narrative: The objective of the Health and Population Project (HPP) is to improve access to and utilization of a package of maternal, neonatal, and child health services in selected governorates with a high concentration of districts with poor health indicators. The Projectwill contribute to the goal of achieving of MDGs 4 (decrease in child mortality) & 5 (improvements in maternal health).

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, A.1 | Description :Steering Committee shall have the overall responsibility for theProject oversight and policy guidance in accordance with the requirements as set out in the Operational Manual (OM). | Frequency:Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, A.2 | Description :The Recipient shall carry out the Project through the DGFH with theassistance of the PAU and the Outreach Services Team, in accordance with the requirements as set out in the OM, FMM and PM. |Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, A.3 | Description :The Recipient shall maintain the Steering Committee, the PAU and theOutreach Services Team, all with a composition, qualifications, experiences and resources satisfactory to IDA. | Frequency:CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, A.4 | Description :For the proper planning and implementations of Parts A.1 and A.3 ofthe Project, the Recipient, shall: (a) not later than June 30,2011, appoint an Independent Technical Auditor (ITA). | Frequency:CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, A.4 | Description :or the proper planning and implementations of Parts A.1 and A.3 of theProject, the Recipient, shall: (a) not later than June 30, 2012, appoint an Independent Technical and Financial Firm (ITFF) |Frequency :CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, B.1 | Description :The Recipient through the GDFH, and with the assistance of the PAU andthe Outreach Services Team, shall carry out the Project in accordance with the requirements and procedures of the ESIA. | Frequency:CONTINUOUS

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, B.2 | Description :Not later than June 30, 2011, the Recipient shall appoint, on termsand conditions satisfactory to IDA, an Environmental Consultantto assist with the implementation of the ESIA and ESMP. | Frequency:CONTINUOUS
